      <h1 class='title'>Biofuels</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='commons-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HC Deb 27 October 2003 vol 412 cc49-50WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_49ws' title='Col. 49WS &mdash; HC Deb 27 October 2003 vol 412 c49WS' name='column_49ws' href='#column_49ws' rel='bookmark'>49WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S6CV0412P0-04759'>
        <a name='S6CV0412P0_20031027_CWS2_234'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-john-hayes' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0412P0_20031027_CWS2_234' title='Link to this speech by Mr John Hayes' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-john-hayes" title="Mr John Hayes">Mr. Hayes</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para" id="S6CV0412P0-04759">To ask the Prime Minister which Government Department is responsible for the formulation of Government policy on biofuels. [134369]</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S6CV0412P0-04760'>
        <a name='S6CV0412P0_20031027_CWS2_235'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-tony-blair' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0412P0_20031027_CWS2_235' title='Link to this speech by Mr Tony Blair' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-tony-blair" title="Mr Tony Blair">The Prime Minister</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para" id="S6CV0412P0-04760">This is a wide-ranging issue in which a number of Departments have an interest.</p><a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_50ws' title='Col. 50WS &mdash; HC Deb 27 October 2003 vol 412 c50WS' name='column_50ws' href='#column_50ws' rel='bookmark'>50WS</a><p id="S6CV0412P0-04761">The Department of Trade and Industry, Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs and the Department for Transport work closely in promoting the Government's policy objectives for the increased use of biofuels.</p><p id="S6CV0412P0-04762">As with all tax issues, responsibility for the fiscal regime on biofuels rests with HM Treasury.</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
